As a product-led organization, Global Nielsen Media puts the product at the center of the strategy and brings cross-functional teams together to work on particular products. With over 2,800 global patents in over 80 countries, the Product team drives value with cutting-edge solutions and analytics to create insights. Be a part of creating the innovative solutions that define the media ecosystem playing field and enable media markets to function

Do you dream of working for one of the leaders in data analytics and media planning software, but
you still have to complete your studies? You’ve come to the right place. Whether you want to take a
break-year before you finalize your study, or you need to collect more credits before starting a new
study, we have the in-between solution for you, as we offer you the opportunity to work part-time on
projects that will help you develop practical skills while being a student.

ABOUT THE JOB 

You will work with various teams and support their challenges and projects, by bringing your own
creative flair. While doing this, you can get hands-on experience and suggest new ways of getting
the job done - faster and better. In addition, you will be part of a smart, international team, and you
will go home every day knowing that you have contributed to the team effort of making a software
tool used all over the planet.
As a student assistant at Nielsen your responsibilities will span from software implementation and
testing to helping the Client Solutions team with various tasks:
 
● Assist with customizing one of our flagship software products Commspoint for our clients
using Python and Excel;
● Making / updating a manual for Commspoint;
● Reproduce errors of clients;
● Help with a variety of tasks for different projects for our clients.
 
ABOUT YOU

● Currently studying Economics, Mathematics, Econometrics, Data Science, or similar;
● Patient and persistent;
● Detail-oriented and well-organized;
● Available for 16-24 hours per week, for at least 6 months;
● Residing in the Netherlands (only).

WHAT WE OFFER

● Competitive salary and benefits;
● Personal and professional development opportunities;
● Flexibility in working hours and location;
● Exciting projects and clients;
● An open, respectful and multicultural atmosphere;
● Time for socializing and fun;
● (when office re-opens) Football and Ping-pong table, and drinks every Friday afternoon;
● 10 days of paid leave annually based on 16h/week employment;

● Reimbursement of traveling expenses
● Daily fruit snacks.
 
FUNCTION HOURS
16-24 hours
